2004: An important earthquake on the western coast of the province of Aceh of Indonesia, on the northern Sumatra, which occurred on 26 December, caused a tsunami that affected 14 countries, causing the death of 226,000 people on the Indian Ocean coast, more than half, in Aceh.
2005: A series of severe earthquakes hit the western coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
