2006: A 6.8-magnitude earthquake struck southern Java, the most populous island in Indonesia, causing a tsunami that devastated the southern coast, resulting in the deaths of nearly 700 people.
2009: A 7.6-magnitude earthquake occurred near the city of Padang, the capital of the province of Western Sumatra.
More than 1,100 people have died.
2010: A 7.5-magnitude earthquake hit the Mentawai Islands, located in front of Sumatra, causing a tsunami of up to 10 meters that destroyed dozens of villages and caused the death of approximately 300 people.
2016: A mild earthquake affected the Pidie Jaya regency, located in Aceh, causing destruction and panic, as people remembered the devastation caused by the 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
